    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab> In nomine Patris et Filii et Spiritu Sancti. Anni ab incarna[t]jone domini
                        nostri Iesu Christi millesimo septuagesimo octavo, regnante domno <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/77">Enricus</persName> rex filius
                        quondam Enritj inperatoris anno viesimo secundo, die nonodetjmo mensis
                        iulii, inditjone prima, in <placeName ref="#places/3524"
                        >Cornido</placeName>. Petivi ad te quidem in Dei nomine domnus <persName
                            key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1599">Geronimus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> de <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Lakes #Fundi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Other_basins #Penalty #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Legumes #Linen #Roads #Fluvial_transport #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie qui vocatur in <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Ponposia</placeName></orgName>, una per consensum
                        deservientjum eiusdem monasterii conceditore, uti michi in Dei nomine
                                <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName> filius
                        quondam <persName><name ref="Gregorius">Gregorius</name></persName> qui
                        manere viso sum in <placeName ref="#places/3544">Arquada</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">libell(i) nomine</rs> concedisti et
                        largisti seu confirmasti michi suprascripto petitore meisque filiis et
                        heredibus rem iuris proprietatis suprascripto monasterio vestro, idest <rs
                            key="#Petiae">petje quinque</rs> de <rs key="#Production">terra
                            aratoria</rs> de rem iuris que abuit et detinuit quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannes de Bonanda">Iohannes qui vocatur de
                            Bonanda</name></persName> pro pagina libelli ad iuris suprascripti
                        monasterii, qui est posite in <rs key="#Fundi">fundo</rs> qui vocatur
                            <geogName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Lakes #Fundi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Other_basins #Penalty #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Legumes #Linen #Roads #Fluvial_transport #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#estates/2445"><placeName
                                key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Lakes #Fundi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Other_basins #Penalty #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Legumes #Linen #Roads #Fluvial_transport #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                ref="#places/3544">Arquada</placeName></geogName> − tres petje ex is
                        que est posite in loco qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Lakes #Fundi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Other_basins #Penalty #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Legumes #Linen #Roads #Fluvial_transport #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#places/4698">Matuni </placeName>. Prima ex is: ab uno ll(atere)
                        po(ssident) heredes quondam <persName key="#Confinia"><name
                                ref="Iohannes de Liudario"> Iohannes qui vocabatur de
                                Lauterio</name></persName>, ha secundo ll(atere) po(ssidet)
                            <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Adam/Balbo"> Adammo qui vocabatur
                                Balbo</name></persName>, ab uno capite <placeName key="#Confinia"
                            ref="#places/3533">Pelestrina</placeName> percorrente; secunda petja ex
                        is: ab uno ll(atere) po(ssident) heredes quondam <persName key="#Confinia"
                                ><name ref="Martinus/de Valerio">Martinus qui vocabatur de
                                Valerio</name></persName>, a tribus lateribus <rs
                            key="#Confinia #Roads">vie plubice</rs> percorrente; tertja vero petja:
                        ab uno ll(atere) poss(ident) heredes quondam Martinus qui vocabatur de
                        Valerio et alio ll(atere) poss(ident) heredes quondam <persName
                            key="#Confinia"><name ref="Paganus">Paganus</name></persName>, ab uno
                        capite Pelestrina percorrente et alio capite via plubica percorrente; quarta
                        vero petja qui est posita in loco qui d(itjtu)r <placeName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Lakes #Fundi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Other_basins #Penalty #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Legumes #Linen #Roads #Fluvial_transport #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#places/4800">Carpini</placeName>: a primo ll(atere) poss(ident)
                        heredes quondam <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Blancus"
                            >Blanco</name></persName> et secundo ll(atere) poss(ident) heredes
                        quondam Paganus, ab uno capite fundo de <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/3948"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Vidrisano</placeName></geogName> et alio capite <persName
                            key="#Confinia"><name ref="Adam/Albo">Adammo qui vocabatur
                            Albo</name></persName>; quinta vero petja est posita in loco qui vocatur
                            <placeName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Lakes #Fundi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Other_basins #Penalty #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Legumes #Linen #Roads #Fluvial_transport #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#places/4801">Tritjuni</placeName>: [ab] uno ll(atere) poss(idet)
                            <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Maria">Maria</name></persName>
                        filia quondam <persName><name ref="Petrus/Maria">Petrus qui vocabatur
                                Maria</name></persName> et a secundo ll(atere) heredes quondam
                            <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Donnellus"
                            >Donnello</name></persName>, ab uno capite poss(ident) heredes quondam
                            <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Iohannes de Vitale">Iohannes qui
                                vocabatur de Vitalis</name></persName> et alio capite poss(ident)
                        heredes quondam <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Wido/Gastaldio">Guido
                                qui vocabatur Gastaldio</name></persName>. Et insuper concedisti
                        michi <rs key="#Lakes #Other_basins">formula</rs> una qui est posita in loco
                        qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Lakes #Other_basins"
                            >Laco</placeName>. Hec omnia ad abendum, tenendum, laborandum,
                        cultandum, <rs key="#Fisheries">piscandum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">venadum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">occupandum</rs>,
                        defensandum et meliorandum in annis advenientibus viginti et novem ad
                        renovandum s[al]va caltjarie domnice dandum, si iuste et ratjon[abili]ter
                        petivi. Ita sane ut inferamus domnice r[atj]onibus tibi suprascripto
                        conceditore tuisque successoribus omni annualiter <rs key="#Levies"
                            >terraticum</rs> de <rs key="#Cereals #Maiores">grano</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Cereals #Maiores">sicale</rs> et <rs key="#Legumes">faba</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Cereals">mesturia ingranata</rs> in campo capa sexta, <rs
                            key="#Cereals #Minores">trisico</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals #Minores"
                            >mileo</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals #Minores">panico</rs> in area modio
                        octavo, <rs key="#Linen">lino</rs> manna detjma gramulata, tritulatum et
                        pervectum ipsum terraticum vestrum domnico per me petitore vel per meis
                        filiis et heredibus que ad ripa ubi <rs key="#Fluvial_transport">nave vestra
                            domnica</rs> potuerit pervenire. Maiore quidem domnico v[estro] vel
                        vestra dominatjone cum onore et obedientjam sussipere debeamus et
                        s[upseptjo]nem ei facere sine dolo vel fraude. Et non a[beamus] licentjam
                        suprascripto petitore meisque filiis et heredibus de [suprascripta] res que
                        superius legitur ad nullum platjtum neque districta ire nisi at te
                        suprascripto conceditore vel ad tuis successoribus; et non abeamus licentjam
                        de ipsa res nec vindere nec donare nec comutuare nisi inter nos fratres et
                        consortes. Si quis vero pars nostra contra hoc petitjonis ire temtaverimus
                        ante perfinitum tempus quod superius legitur, det pars parti fidem servandi
                        ante omnis litis initjum vel interpell(atjonem), pene nomine, <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri obtimi untja una</rs> et post penam solutam
                        permanead ec pe[titjo]nis in suo robore et firmitatis. Quam ve[ro pa]ginam
                            <persName key="#Tabellio"><name ref="Rodulfus"/>Rodulfus</persName> in
                        Dei nomine <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> [de <rs key="#Vici">vico</rs>
                        qui vocatur] <placeName key="#Vici" ref="#places/4699">Pupiniano</placeName>
                        scribendum rogavi et sup[ter ma]nu mea propria firmavi tam tibi suprascripto
                        conce[di]tore tradidit, sub die, mense et inditjone suprascripta prima.
                        Singnum manus suprascripto Iohannes petitore ad omnia suprascripta cui
                        relectum est.</ab>
                </div>
